      "content": "but what if they aren't just using standard consumer tech? you said \"not typically in common use\", which implies it's possible. if someone wanted to monitor someone else's movement through walls using radio frequency oscillations or something like Wi-Fi sensing, wouldn't that look exactly like what i'm seeing?",
